default&#xa0;defaultQuality as a matter of custom – 
defaults.36 (
default10)
defaultThe first concern which UKCTA has relates to 
defaultsection 36(10) which provides that “A contract to provide digital content may be treated as making provision about the quality of the digital content as a matter of custom.”
defaultUKCTA does not believe that it is appropriate to infer that any provision is made 
defaultbased on custom. One of the key 
defaultcharacteristics
default of the market for digital content is that it is continuously evolving and that the pace of change is rapid. The reference to custom might be appropriate in a more static market but it is not appropriate in re
defaultlation to the provision of digital content. UKCTA would therefore suggest that sub section 10 
defaultought to be
default deleted.
